SIMPLE: untruth
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Untruth
<hw>Un*truth"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality of being untrue; contrariety to truth; want of veracity; also,
treachery; faithlessness; disloyalty.</def>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is untrue; a false assertion; a
falsehood; a lie; also, an act of treachery or disloyalty.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Lie; falsehood. See <er>Lie</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Untruthful</ent>⟦br⟧
